social_posts.post_text: Vermillion Red Flower (2020) from the series: Portraits of Plants. 100x140cm. 〰️🔴

Vuoden kuvittaja 2023! Illustrator of the year 2023! I’m very glad to announce that I’ve been chosen as the illustrator of the year by the Finnish Illustration Association. Many thanks to the jury, @kuvittajat_ry and @kopiosto for this great honor! ❤️

I’d like to thank everyone who has been supporting my journey this far. Clients, friends, family, colleagues, collaborators and my dear agent of course. I’ve been now working as an illustrator for almost 10 years and hoping to continue as long as possible. Here’s for the next decade 🍾🥰🌞

•

“Stunning use of colour, clarity of form and a refined sense of style. The ability to simplify so that the images do not seem calculated. A recognisable yet versatile style that naturally lends hitself to canvases, posters and book covers. A light and relaxed language of form and elegant colour harmony. A fresh take on the traditions of poster art. Warmth and tenderness in shapes and colours.” This is how the jury justifies its choice of Illustrator of the Year 2023. Antti Kalevi’s light and relaxed language of form and elegant colour harmony are inspired by modernism but filtered into the modern age. The jury believes that many of Antti Kalevi’s works are on the borderline between art and illustration.

For Antti Kalevi, Illustrator of the Year, ease of creation is more important than the finishing touches. According to the jury, everything about Antti Kalevi’s work seems freely and joyfully executed. “I myself think that if I have fun when I create images, I believe and hope that it will be conveyed on some level and that others will also enjoy looking at them,” the new Illustrator of the Year tells Kuvittaja Magazine. In addition to the monetary prize, the Illustrator of the Year will be awarded an exhibition of their work. Antti Kalevi’s work has previously been exhibited in Helsinki, Tokyo and Seoul, among other locations. His Award Exhibition will be displayed in Helsinki in autumn 2023.”

New work for @kirsikkahelsinki 🥬🍅🍸🍋🥦 I was happy to create a series of illustrations for restaurant Kirsikka which was opened about a month ago to the newly renovated Hakaniemi market hall in Helsinki. Each season the restaurants menu covers and drinklist will have my illustration, all illustrated with each season’s ingredients. Many thanks for the wonderful project @villerelander & @jonnavormala ❤️ Thank you also AD @paulik @minna_malinen @petrakoivisto 🌸🌞first and second photo by @mf3000 / Miltton

STUDY WITH CIRCLES (2023)
2 x 100x160cm, Print on film

AIKA OK, Grafia 90 years – New work on display at @luonnostila gallery in Helsinki until 12.11.2023. Congratulations @grafia_ry and many thanks for having me! ⚫️
 •

FI/ Idea tälle kokeelliselle kalvotyölle syntyi aikaisin kesäisenä aamuna. Teos tutkii tyhjää tilaa ja muodon syvyysvaikutelmaa tilassa.

Miltä näyttää kun kahdelle läpinäkyvälle kalvolle tulostetut ilmassa roikkuvat pisteet asetetaan tilassa peräkkäin? Toisessa kalvossa on reikä jonka toinen täydentää. Yhdessä ne muodostavat ympyrän. Tyhjä tila täyttyy. Ympyrät täyttävät ympyrän.

•

ENG/ The idea for this experimental work came about early one summer morning. The work studies the relationship between empty space and the perception of depth in space.

What does it look like when two films with printed small circles are placed in a space behind one another? One film has an empty circle which the other one makes full. Together they form a circle. Empty space fills up. The circles form a circle.
  •  Special thanks for the exhibition curators: Ilona Ilottu, Esa Matinvesi and Katja Merisalo. The exgibition also includes work from Saana Hellsten, Veera Kortelainen, Hannu Kyyriäinen, Laura Matikainen, Esa Ojala and Piëtke Visser.   Exhibition architecture: Antti Auvinen Installation: Ville Auvinen
Visual Identity: Tomi Leppänen Production: Essi Lax Communications: Essi Lax ja Katja Ojala
